>>894183335
This makes more sense. They're finding that medical strains if weed (that is, ones with higher CBD) give many chronic pain patients similar pain relief as opioid pain killers, but with way less serious addiction potential and almost no possibility of overdose leading to death.
I'm not saying it's perfect, of course. You can still get addicted from using it long term. But the addiction is way less severe. I've been badly addicted to weed before and the worst symptoms are boredom when you'd normally do it, and up to a week of shitty sleep and somewhat worse anxiety after you go cold turkey. The sleep was the worst part for me. The anxiety was obnoxious until I realized it was just caused by weed withdrawal and then it reduced by a lot, since anxiety feeds into itself and gets way worse if you think it's over something real. It's not pleasant, but it's nowhere near opioid withdrawal where you practically need treatment to get over it. And too much weed can trigger cardiovascular events but you have to already be just about on the brink already -- it doesn't do anything particularly special, just temporarily raised blood pressure and heart rate during the phase where you feel high. Aside from that, you might feel like you're dead if you had way too much of it, but you ultimately just have a bad time and then you're fine when you sober up.
So yeah, I wouldn't be surprised if they make a prescription form of it that chronic pain sufferers can get through their insurance, either as oil packaged into a pill, or as raw herb like the medical marijuana stuff mostly is now.

>>894173387
Are you male or female and are you looking to get a male or female dog? Are you looking to get the dog as a puppy or adopt an adult?

>German Shepherd
SS tier. There's a reason GSDs are the #1 breed for zoos. Their loyalty and protectiveness go into overdrive when they see you as a mate. They also look great physically. They are super easy to train, but you HAVE to train them. You can't be lazy with Shepherds or else they try to own you (which may sound hot, but it's not)

>Border/Aussies
They need a job. If you live someplace and own smaller livestock like Goats and Sheep, great. If not, they will get bored quick.

>Goldens (and Labradors)
Great starter breeds, they embody the saying "Whole of heart, dumb of ass". I personally love Shepherds for their intelligence, it feels like he's my companion in life, not just a pet. While Goldens look great physically, I still prefer the smarts of a Shepherd.
